'''Ken Aitken''' (25 June 1928 – June 2008) was an [[Australian rules football]]er who played with [[Carlton Football Club|Carlton]] and [[Collingwood Football Club|Collingwood]] in the [[Australian Football League|Victorian Football League]] (VFL).

Aitken never played more than nine games in a seasons for the seniors but was a member of Carlton's 1951 premiership team in the league seconds.<ref name=AFLTables>[http://stats.rleague.com/afl/stats/players/K/Ken_Aitken.html AFL Tables: Ken Aitken]</ref> He joined Collingood the following year and was a reserve in the [[1952 VFL Grand Final]], which they lost.<ref name=AFLTables/>

He was dropped from Collingwood's list in the pre-season and signed with the [[Coburg Football Club]].<ref>''[[The Age]]'',[http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/23424676 "Coburg has worry"], 4 August 1954, p. 22</ref> After retiring he was coach of the Carlton Under-19s side for four years, from 1956 to 1959

